businesses - 61% of retailers report 25%+ revenue from outside core offering TARGET MARKET SEGMENTS: 1. Portfolio career professionals (growing trend, replacing traditional jobs) 2. Multi-hyphenate entrepreneurs (food service, retail, creative industries) 3. Gen Z founders (building while in school) 4. Creator economy workers (88% expect more income than last year) 5. Professionals with side hustles transitioning to full multi-hyphenate COMPETITIVE LANDSCAPE: Visual Canvas Tools: Miro, Mural, Milanote, Canva PKM Tools: Notion ($15-20/mo), Obsidian (free + $4-8/mo premium), Roam Research ($15/mo), Tana ($10-12/mo), Coda Brain Dump/Idea Capture: ClickUp, Goblin.tools, Reflect, WorkFlowy GAP IN MARKET: - No tool specifically addresses multi-hyphenate creative needs - Existing tools either focus on visual canvas OR structured data, not both seamlessly - No integrated system for brain dump → organization → execution specifically for multiple simultaneous projects/identities - Missing: AI-powered idea connection detection across multiple domains - Missing: Swipe file/library functionality integrated with canvas thinking MONETIZATION: - Freemium: Free tier for basic capture + 1 canvas - Core: $10-15/mo (aligned with Tana/Roam pricing) - Pro: $25-35/mo (unlimited canvases, AI features, templates) - Enterprise/Teams: Custom pricing - Affiliate partnerships: Notion, productivity tools - Template marketplace (revenue share) - Could also develop proprietary SaaS Now I'll create detailed tactical plan with implementation roadmap. View Now I'll create comprehensive visual business framework with charts and detailed tactical implementation plan: Using Tool | MCP Chart Server MCP: generate_mind_map {\"data\":{\"name\":\"Multi-Hyphenate Creative Platform\",\"children\":[{\"name\":\"Core Features\",\"children\":[{\"name\":\"Idea Capture System\",\"children\":[{\"name\":\"Quick Brain Dump Interface\"},{\"name\":\"Voice-to-Text Capture\"},{\"name\":\"Mobile Quick Add\"},{\"name\":\"Ema