ntent\t$45,000\t$120,000\t$250,000\tContent, ads, tools, partnerships Infrastructure (hosting, APIs)\t$10,000\t$35,000\t$85,000\tScaling with usage Operations & Admin\t$15,000\t$40,000\t$80,000\tLegal, accounting, tools Customer Support\t$10,000\t$35,000\t$75,000\tChat support + success team Total Operating Costs\t$200,000\t$430,000\t$840,000 Net Profit/(Loss)\t($130,800)\t$145,240\t$1,015,200 Burn Rate\t$10,900/mo\tBreak-even Month 14\tProfitable Funding Strategy Bootstrap Path (Recommended for Validation): Months 1-6: Self-funded MVP development ($20-30K personal investment) Months 7-12: Revenue reinvestment + small angel round ($50-100K) if traction proven Year 2: Seed round ($500K-1M) once product-market fit validated Alternatively - Affiliate Model First: Build audience through content (6 months) Promote existing tools (Notion, Tana) as affiliate Use affiliate revenue ($2-5K/mo) to fund development Launch own platform once audience = 10K+ email subscribers KEY PERFORMANCE INDICATORS (KPIs) North Star Metric \"Ideas Executed\" = Ideas captured → moved to action → completed Primary KPIs Dashboard Category\tMetric\tMonth 3 Target\tMonth 6 Target\tMonth 12 Target\tTracking Method Acquisition\tWebsite visitors\t2,500\t7,500\t25,000\tGoogle Analytics Waitlist signups\t1,000\t3,000\tN/A (launched)\tCRM Free signups\t500\t2,500\t8,000\tProduct analytics Activation\tComplete onboarding\t70%\t75%\t80%\tPosthog funnels Create first canvas\t60%\t70%\t75%\tProduct events Add 10+ ideas\t40%\t50%\t60%\tProduct events Engagement\tWeekly active users (WAU)\t35% of users\t45%\t55%\tProduct analytics Ideas captured/user/week\t8\t12\t15\tDatabase query Canvases created/user\t2\t3\t5\tDatabase query Retention\tDay 7 retention\t40%\t50%\t60%\tCohort analysis Day 30 retention\t25%\t30%\t40%\tCohort analysis Month 3 retention\tN/A\t20%\t30%\tCohort analysis Monetization\tFree → Paid conversion\t3%\t5%\t7%\tPayment analytics Core → Pro upgrade\t15%\t20%\t25%\tPayment analytics Monthly churn rate\t<10%\t<7%\t<5%\tSubscription analytics Revenue\tMRR\t$0\t$1,800\t$5,800\tStripe dashboard MRR growth rate\tN/A\t30%+\t40%+\tMonth-over-month RISK ANALYSIS & MITIGATION Risk Category\tSpecific Risk\tProbability\tImpact\tMitigation Strategy Market\tNotion/Miro adds similar features\tMedium\tHigh\t- Move fast on AI differentiation - Build community moat - Focus on multi-hyphenate niche positioning Technical\tAI costs exceed projections\tHigh\tMedium\t- Implement usage caps per tier - Optimize prompts for efficiency - Consider open-source models (Llama 3) Acquisition\tCAC higher than projected\tMedium\tHigh\t- Double down on organic (SEO, community) - Build referral program early - Create viral template marketplace Product\tUsers don't adopt canvas thinking\tLow\tHigh\t- Strong onboarding with templates - Video tutorials showing benefits - Offer \"traditional\" list view option Financial\tRunway runs out before profitability\tMedium\tCritical\t- Bootstrap longer before raising - Monetize earlier with consulting - Affiliate revenue bridge Team\tCan't hire fast enough\tMedium\tMedium\t- Start with contractors - Use no-code tools initially - Outsource non-core functions Legal\tData privacy/compliance issues\tLow\tHigh\t- SOC 2 compliance from start - GDPR-ready architecture - Clear ToS and data policies MVP DEVELOPMENT: STEP-BY-STEP TACTICAL SOP PHASE 1: PRE-DEVELOPMENT (Weeks 1-2) Step\tAction Required\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tTools Needed\tTime 1.1\tCreate detailed feature specification document\t- Research notes - Competitor analysis - User interviews (5-10)\t20-page feature spec with user stories\tGoogle Docs, Figma\t20 hours 1.2\tDesign information architecture\t- Feature spec - User flow sketches\tSitemap + database schema diagram\tWhimsical, Draw.io\t8 hours 1.3\tCreate wireframes for all core screens\t- Information architecture - Design inspiration\t15-20 wireframes (low-fidelity)\tFigma, Balsamiq\t16 hours 1.4\tDesign high-fidelity mockups\t- Wireframes - Brand identity\t10-12 pixel-perfect screens\tFigma\t24 hours 1.5\tSet up development environment\t- Tech stack decisions - GitHub account\t- Repository initialized - CI/CD pipeline - Staging environment\tGitHub, Vercel, Railway\t6 hours 1.6\tCreate project roadmap\t- Feature priorities - Team capacity\tGantt chart with milestones\tNotion, ClickUp\t4 hours Total Phase 1 Time: 78 hours (2 weeks if full-time, 4-6 weeks if part-time) PHASE 2: MVP DEVELOPMENT (Weeks 3-12) Step\tAction Required\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tTools Needed\tTime 2.1\tBuild authentication system\t- Design mockups - User flow\tWorking signup/login with email + Google/GitHub OAuth\tClerk/Auth0, React\t16 hours 2.2\tCreate database schema\t- Data model diagram - Feature requirements\tPostgreSQL tables + relationships set up\tSupabase/Railway, SQL\t12 hours 2.3\tBuild idea capture interface\t- Quick-add mockup - API endpoints\tFast input form with save functionality\tReact, Express\t20 hours 2.4\tImplement AI categorization\t- OpenAI API key - Training examples\tIdeas auto-tagged by category\tOpenAI API, Python/Node\t24 hours 2.5\tBuild infinite canvas engine\t- Canvas mockups - Interaction designs\tDrag-and-drop, zoom, pan canvas\tFabric.js/Konva, React\t40 hours 2.6\tCreate card/idea components\t- Design system - Canvas integration\tDraggable idea cards on canvas\tReact components\t16 hours 2.7\tBuild swipe file upload system\t- File storage setup - Upload UI\tMulti-format file upload + preview\tS3/R2, React Dropzone\t20 hours 2.8\tImplement AI tagging for files\t- Vision API setup - Audio transcription\tAuto-tags for images, videos, audio\tOpenAI Vision, Whisper\t16 hours 2.9\tBuild search functionality\t- Search index setup - UI design\tFast full-text search across ideas + files\tTypesense, React\t20 hours 2.10\tCreate template system\t- 5 starter templates - Template data structure\tPre-built canvases users can clone\tJSON templates, database\t16 hours 2.11\tBuild settings & profile pages\t- User settings mockup - Subscription logic\tAccount management interface\tReact, Stripe\t12 hours 2.12\tImplement Stripe subscription\t- Pricing tiers - Payment flow\tWorking payment processing\tStripe API\t16 hours 2.13\tBuild responsive mobile views\t- Mobile designs - Desktop codebase\tMobile-optimized interfaces\tTailwind CSS\t24 hours 2.14\tTesting & bug fixes\t- QA test plan - Beta tester feedback\tStable, bug-free MVP\tTesting tools, Sentry\t40 hours Total Phase 2 Time: 292 hours (10 weeks with 1 full-time dev, 20+ weeks if solo part-time) PHASE 3: LAUNCH PREPARATION (Weeks 13-16) Step\tAction Required\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tTools Needed\tTime 3.1\tWrite product documentation\t- Feature spec - Screenshots\tHelp center with 20+ articles\tNotion, Gitbook\t20 hours 3.2\tCreate video tutorials\t- Script outlines - Screen recording\t5-7 explainer videos (5-10 min each)\tLoom, Descript\t24 hours 3.3\tSet up analytics tracking\t- KPI list - Event taxonomy\tFull event tracking implemented\tPosthog, Mixpanel\t8 hours 3.4\tLaunch beta program\t- Beta application form - Onboarding email sequence\t50 active beta testers providing feedback\tTypeform, Mailchimp\t12"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=2c4a335a-ef6d-4a19-9d56-47511d7ec66b","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=2c4a335a-ef6d-4a19-9d56-47511d7ec66b"}]}]}]
